#  Netflix Data Analysis (EDA Project)

##  What this project is about
This project explores Netflix’s dataset to understand trends in movies and TV shows. I analyzed the data to find patterns like most watched genres, content distribution, and release trends.

##  Why I built this
I wanted to practice real-world data analysis and understand how companies use data to make decisions about content.

##  Dataset
Netflix movies and TV shows dataset (CSV format)

##  Tools I used
- Python  
- Pandas  
- Matplotlib  
- Seaborn  

##  What I did in this project
- Cleaned missing and duplicate data  
- Explored movie vs TV show distribution  
- Analyzed top genres  
- Studied release year trends  
- Created visual charts for insights  

##  Key Insights
- Most content on Netflix is movies  
- Drama and Comedy are the most common genres  
- Content increased rapidly after 2015  

##  What I learned
This project helped me understand how exploratory data analysis works and how to extract meaningful insights from raw data.

